.TH "fsl_chan_set_src_loop_size" 9 "fsl_chan_set_src_loop_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_chan_set_src_loop_size \- Set source address hold transfer size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fsl_chan_set_src_loop_size
.BI "(struct fsldma_chan *chan "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chan" 12
Freescale DMA channel
.IP "size" 12
Address loop size, 0 for disable loop
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The set source address hold transfer size. The source
address hold or loop transfer size is when the DMA transfer
data from source address (SA), if the loop size is 4, the DMA will
read data from SA, SA + 1, SA + 2, SA + 3, then loop back to SA,
SA + 1 ... and so on.
